  "text": "Gels were then carefully washed with double-distilled water, scanned at an optical resolution of 300 dpi (or 600 dpi), and saved as.tiff files. For spot detection and volume quantification, 300 dpi.tiff files were analyzed using the PDQuest software version 7.4. To correct for variability in CBB staining, the individual spot volumes were normalized by dividing each spot's optical density (OD) value by the sum total OD of all the spots in the respective gels. Automated and manual spot matching were also performed [CITATION_1] .",
